      <div xml:id="NA206-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">itu talaimakaṉ ciṟaippuṟattāṉākac tōḻi colliyatu.</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">This is what the confidante said when HE was behind the fence.</p>
      </div>
      <div xml:id="NA206">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>            tuyttalaip puṉiṟṟukkural pālvār piṟaiñcit</l>
<l>            tōṭalaik koṇṭaṉa vēṉa leṉṟu</l>
<l>            tuṟukaṉ mīmicaik kuṟuvaṉa kuḻīic</l>
<l>            cevvāyp pāciṉaṅ kavarumeṉ ṟavvāyt</l>
<l>            taṭṭaiyum puṭaittaṉai kavaṇaiyun toṭukkeṉa </l>
<l>            ventaivan turaittaṉa ṉāka vaṉṉaiyu</l>
<l>            naṉṉāḷ vēṅkaiyu malarkamā viṉiyeṉa</l>
<l>            veṉmuka nōkkiṉa ḷevaṉko ṟōḻi</l>
<l>            celvā ḷeṉṉuṅkol ceṟippa leṉṉuṅkol</l>
<l>            kalkeḻu nāṭaṉ kēṇmai </l>
<l>            yaṟintaṉaḷ kollaḵ taṟikaleṉ yāṉē.</l>
            </lg>
        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l rend="indent2">When my father came,</l>
<l rend="indent">[thinking] “the millet [plants] have come to sway in masses,</l>
<l rend="indent">[their] cotton-headed newly born ears bowing, overflowing with milk”<note place="foot">The subtle syntax especially of the first two lines is once again far from clear. The most natural thing is to connect <term xml:lang="ta">koṇṭaṉa</term> with <term xml:lang="ta">ēṉal</term>., and explain the plural as the single millet plants. But what is the meaning of <term xml:lang="ta">koḷ</term> here? Do we simply have to understand the auxiliary here, as giving a reflexive nuance to the <term xml:lang="ta">alai</term>?</note>,</l>
<l rend="indent">[and] “crowding on the height of thick stones, [ready] to pluck,	</l>
<l rend="indent">the green group of red-beaks will seize [our crop]”</l>
<l rend="indent4">[and] said “in that place</l>
<l rend="indent">you may thrash the Taṭṭai [and] put together the sling”</l>
<l rend="indent4">mother too</l>
<l>looked at my face, saying</l>
<l rend="indent2">“may the Vēṅkai too blossom on a good day now”.</l>
<l rend="indent3">What [of this], friend?</l>
<l>Does it mean “she may go”? Does it mean “I shall keep [her] back”?</l>
<l rend="indent">[Our] intimacy with the man from the stony land,</l>
<l>has she understood it? That I do not know.</l>
        </lg>
      </div>
